                        <note>text of CIL. At l.7 Caietanus suggests Dulcisius</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#AR">
                <p>Per la felicità dei tempi dei nostri signori Constanzo e Constante gli Augusti, i viri clarissimi consolari della provincia di Sicilia, Vitrasio Orfito e Flavio Dulcizio, costruirono un posto di guardia dalle fondamenta, sotto il controllo di Flavio Valeriano in qualità di ducenario, commissario imperiale nella pubblica amministraione e comandante del servizio di posta</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AR">
                <p>In return for the fortune of the time of our lords Constantius and Constans, the consulars of the Sicilian Province, Vitrasius Orfitus and Flavius Dulcitius, both men of oustanding merit, constructed a way-station from the ground up. (This was done) under the auspices of Flavius Valerianus, functioning as Ducenarius, commissioner in the public administration and chief of the postal service</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>For contextual discussion, cf. commentary of <ref target="http://ppret-inscriptions.huma-num.fr/en/inscriptions/ppret49.html">PPRET 49</ref> = CIL 5.8987.
                    <!--building of a statio, by two consulares prov. Sic. Flavius Dulcitius and Memmius Vitrasius Orfitus; NB a parallel text now found at Marsala, for which Silvestrini (2014a)--></p>
            </div>
